folder: Sullivan Street & Grand Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Sullivan Street, west side, north from and including No. 26, north of Grand Street, seen from the S.E. corner, shortly before demolition of the buildings in the left foreground. One of the old houses to go will be 46 Sullivan Street (42 Watts Street), the frame house at the N.W. corner of Watts Street, the first intersection north of the observer.
1926.

folder: Grand Street & Sullivan Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Grand Street, north side, east from Sullivan Street.
About 1927.

folder: 6th Avenue & Canal Street & Grand Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, north from above Canal Street, showing constructional details of this new diagonal extension and its subway underground. Grand Street is in the midground and the buildings there face on both sides of same. These extend east to Thompson Street. View 2 is photographed at Grand Street.

October 19, 1928
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr
title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - Canal Street - Grand Street

folder: Manhattan : 6th Avenue & Grand & Canal Streets., Manhattan, NY
text:
Sixth Ave., east side, south from and including Grand, to and including Canal Streets. Also shown is Grand Street, south side, east from Sixth Ave., to and including Thompson Street. Nos. 29-31 Grand Street, adjoining and west of the S.W. corner of Thompson Street are frame houses. Also shown is the rear of St. Alphonsus Roman Catholic Church and School, through clearance for the widening of Sixth Ave.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York. Negative No. 307.
title: Manhattan : 6th Avenue - Grand - Canal Streets.
